# cv-infra — NVIDIA driver branch pin (decision 2026-07-03-driver-r580-realignment).
#
# WHY: Isaac Sim 5.1.0 (kit 107.3.3) deterministically segfaults in the RTX
# renderer (librtx.scenedb.plugin.so, ~50ms after "app ready") on the R595
# driver branch — confirmed upstream as a known issue with no workaround. The
# branch Isaac 5.1.0 is certified against is R580 (LTSB, EOL 2028-06). This
# file (a) holds every R580 userspace component at the realignment target and
# (b) hard-blocks the R595/R610 branches so a routine `apt upgrade` /
# unattended-upgrades can never re-ascend past R580 (the original incident:
# a floor-only ">= 580.65.06" assert admitted 595.71.05).
#
# Canonical copy: cv-infra-workspace/scripts/workstation_setup/apt-preferences-cv-infra-nvidia-r580
# Deployed to:    /etc/apt/preferences.d/cv-infra-nvidia-r580 (by realign_driver_r580.sh)
#
# NOTE: per-kernel module packages (linux-modules-nvidia-580-open-<kver>) carry
# KERNEL version numbers, so stanza 1 deliberately does not version-hold them —
# they must track kernel updates; their branch is fixed by the package name.

# 1) Hold all R580 userspace components at the stage-1 target build
#    (realign_driver_r580.sh --stage2 rewrites this stanza to 580.65.06*).
Package: *nvidia*580*
Pin: version 580.159.03*
Pin-Priority: 1001

# 2) Never install anything from the R595 branch (Isaac 5.1.0 RTX segfault).
Package: *nvidia*595*
Pin: version *
Pin-Priority: -1

# 3) Never install anything from the R610 branch (uncertified for Isaac 5.1.0).
Package: *nvidia*610*
Pin: version *
Pin-Priority: -1
